= Load Sequence VDBs =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Loads a VDB file sequence into a USD stage as a Volume and OpenVDB primitive."""

== Overview ==

Load Sequence VDBs creates a USD layer containing a Volume primitive and a child OpenVDB primitive. The `filePath` property on the OpenVDB primitive is time-sampled to match the VDB file sequence frame range.

WARNING:
    No extent (bounding box) data is written. Downstream consumers relying on `extentsHint` will not receive bounds information from this node. Use __Manually Set ExtentsHint__ to add it if needed.

@parameters

Parent Primitive:
    #id: parent_primpath
    Root path under which the Volume primitive will be created.

Primitive Name:
    #id: prim_name
    Name of the Volume primitive. The OpenVDB primitive will be created as a child of this prim.

VDB Files:
    #id: files
    File path pattern for the VDB sequence. Supports `$F` frame substitution.

Start/End:
    #id: frame_range
    Frame range of the VDB sequence.

Grids:
    #id: grids
    Space-separated list of VDB grid names to include in the OpenVDB primitive.

Grid Index:
    #id: grid_index
    Index of the grid within the VDB file. Usually `0`. Increase if multiple grids share the same name.
